now.”

Martin reached for a newspaper lying on a nearby table. It turned out to be a Russian émigré one, published in Paris.

“How’s school?” asked Zilanov, without raising his eyes from the evenly running pen.

“Pretty good,” said Martin, putting down the paper. “How long have they been out?” Zilanov did not answer: the pen was going at full tilt. A few minutes later, though, he spoke again, still not looking at Martin. “Idling away your time, I imagine. Only thing colleges 